problem:
Three concentric circles are shown. The two largest circles have radii of $21$ and $29.$ If the area of the ring between the two largest circles equals the area of the smallest circle, determine the radius of the smallest circle.

[asy]
import graph;
filldraw(circle((0,0),12), lightgray, black+linewidth(1));
filldraw(circle((0,0),10), white, black+linewidth(1));
filldraw(circle((0,0),6), gray, black+linewidth(1));
dot((0,0));
[/asy]
